programme.desc: We like to call it soul food. This program uses creative illustration, real life stories and biblical teaching to encourage and help viewers discover a greater purpose to their lives.

programme.title: Drive Thru History
programme.sub-title: The Book Closes on the New Testament Period
programme.desc: In this series of Drive Thru History, Dave Stotts explores the amazing lives of the very first Christians. Beginning in Jerusalem and using the Book of Acts as a roadmap, Dave travels the Mediterranean region to share the people, places, and events that launched the Christian faith. He investigates what happened after the Gospel accounts of Jesus Christ. Dave follows the lives of the disciples through Israel, and travels the missionary routes of Paul and his companions. We finish with John on the island of Patmos, and drive through the seven churches of Revelation in Asia Minor.

programme.title: Joyce Meyer: Enjoying Everyday Life
programme.sub-title: You Are Full of Good Things - Part 2
programme.desc: Do you enjoy life or do you constantly struggle with guilt and condemnation? Discover the difference between conviction and condemnation, and learn how to enjoy every day of your life!

programme.title: Convocation
programme.desc: Convocation at Liberty University is North Americas largest weekly gathering of Christian students, and each year it plays host to more than 80 guest speakers of national significance from every sphere of society. The services, held within the Vines Centre at the University during each semester, connect students with their Creator through passionate worship and powerful messages firmly rooted in Biblical truth.

programme.title: When Calls the Heart
programme.desc: Allie makes a daring decision, and Nathan and Elizabeth rush to intervene. Uncovered memories shift Lucass plans. Faith takes a big step. Mei cooks for Hickams family.

programme.title: Welcome to Hope
programme.desc: John tries to act as though everything is normal, but Abe is looking for someone to blame for the Potter family misfortunes.

programme.title: Breath of Life
programme.desc: Every breath we take is a miracle and tells us something profound about the nature of God. Breath of Life features leading voices from the worlds of faith and creativity. An original series based on Daniel Koomans inspiring book Breath of Life: Three Breaths that Shaped Humanity, this 3-part series features The Chosen TV Series Creator Dallas Jenkins, Trevor McNevan of Thousand Foot Krutch, Korey Cooper and Jen Ledger from Skillet, Kim Walker-Smith of Jesus Culture Music, Astronomer Dr Hugh Ross, Rabbi Kirt Schneider of Discovering The Jewish Jesus, and Dr Fazale Rana from Reasons to Believe. A profound new series that reveals what it means to be made in Gods image and how to inhale the living breath of God.

programme.title: Owlegories
programme.desc: Owlegories is an animated series that follows a group of student owls as they travel on adventures learning about nature, faith, and God! You can tell a lot about an artist by what he creates. That is the theme behind Owlegories. Owlegories teaches kids about God through the amazing things found in nature and revealed in Gods word. The banner verse for Owlegories is Psalm 19:1-4: "The heavens declare the glory of God; the skies proclaim the work of his hands. Day after day they pour forth speech; night after night they reveal knowledge. They have no speech, they use no words; no sound is heard from them. Yet their voice goes out into all the earth, their words to the ends of the world."

programme.title: Superbook
programme.desc: The familiar and the futuristic interact with ancient people, places and events to create a sense of wonder, anticipation, empowerment, and personal breakthrough as the children witness Gods interaction with man. Superbook is always an exciting journey, full of discovery - with a transformational outcome. Superbook teaches children timeless moral truths and life lessons through the captivating, Bible-based adventures of two time-traveling children and their robot friend. Play fun Superbook games here: https://us-en.superbook.cbn.com/games.

programme.title: Friends and Heroes
programme.desc: Friends and Heroes is an animated childrens adventure based in Ancient Egypt, Israel and Rome. The story follows two young friends Macky and Portia as they fight for justice against the Roman Empire.

programme.title: Jentezen Franklin
programme.sub-title: How to Redeem Your Family Name Series Part 2
programme.desc: New York Times bestselling author, Pastor Jentezen Franklin, brings practical meaning to spiritual truths found in Gods Word. Kingdom Connection is the teaching ministry of Free Chapel, a multi-campus church with a global ministry. Hear inspiration for change, healing, peace and joy through his affective communication connecting you to God, the church, and the world!

programme.title: Centuries Collide
programme.sub-title: St Nicholas - St Nick or Santa?
programme.desc: Every year, baby Jesus and Santa dominate all Christmas imagery. But who is this jolly fur-clad mythological figure? In this episode we discover his fascinating 1700 year evolution from a bishop of ancient Turkey to Santa Clause of the North Pole.

programme.title: TV4DADs
programme.desc: The TV4DADS team head to Florida. In Season 6 of the program, Brian teams up with his daughter Jeni (from Jeni:Seeking the Extraordinary) for an adventure in Florida that sees them catching fish, throwing axes, and being ambushed by killer birds.

programme.title: View and Chew
programme.desc: The Empire State strikes back with an all out pizza vs pizza extravaganza. From old classics to wild combinations, Allie and Kels try all the pizza NYC has to offer.

programme.title: Be Great. Do Good
programme.desc: There is a myth when it comes to business leadership of the "self-made" leader that lacks credibility. The reality is that all leaders are shaped and influenced by others. And to avoid being a leader that is successful, but in achieving success has ended up alone and empty, its important to be influenced by the right people. Peter dives deep with Mike Magyar from Daniels Health about the value of developing relationships and connecting with mentors that care for you as a person, as well as the businesses success. And how when these are the right people, they will help make you the leader you want to be. Peter and the team breakdown how wanting to be self-made can have a wider negative impact, even if the business is a success.

programme.title: Compassion Stories
programme.desc: Follow powerful stories highlighting the transformative work of the Compassion Child Sponsorship Program in Africa, South America, India and Asia. Gain insight and inspiration through the honest eyes of those directly affected in this compelling series, Compassion Stories. Hear about the journey of individuals and families as they search for hope in their different circumstances of poverty and desperation.

programme.title: A Cathedral Pilgrimage
programme.desc: Dominating the landscape for centuries, ancient cathedrals and abbeys reflect Britains turbulent history through their architectural grandeur. A Pilgrimage through Britains Great Cathedrals explores cathedrals and abbeys found throughout England and Wales, featuring interviews with historians and experts and breathtaking footage of the cathedrals legendary facades and soaring interior spaces.

programme.title: The Good Road
programme.desc: The Good Road goes to space! - well almost. We go to Cape Canaveral Space Force Station to learn about the critical role of the newly created Space Force. Space Force Guardians protect national security and oversee all launches. We discover the surprising role they play in our everyday lives.

programme.title: Planetshakers TV
programme.desc: Planetshakers mission is to empower a generation to win a generation. This Christian youth movement began as an annual conference in Melbourne that saw thousands of people of different ages, backgrounds and nationalities from all over the globe gather together. The movement grew and grew into an international ministry and church. Russell and Sam Evans are the senior pastors of Planetshakers City Church and Planetshakers TV showcases weekly teaching and music.

programme.sub-title: Positioned In His Protection Pt 3 of 4

programme.desc: Lizzie Oakes invites her guests into honest conversations about difficult seasons in their lives and discovers how the light of Gods love got them through.

Paige and Ben clash over their ideas for production but realise they must grapple with the fact that not only do they need each other to further their careers, but they also balance each other on and off the screen.

programme.title: A New Years Resolution
programme.desc: Kelly Leone, producer at a local morning television talk show, has made it her mission to make her show a success. Shes done a great job, but her dedication has meant her friendships and her bigger career goals have suffered. On New Years Eve, her best friends AJ, Lisa and Jackson, pressure her to make a New Years resolution: to say yes to any social invitation offered to her, no matter the event. The end date of this resolution is her thirtieth birthday in one months time. Much to her chagrin, her production team, looking for an extended New Years story for the show, decides to follow her for the month. The resolution coincides with Kelly meeting Tom Malone, a marketing director at the regional office of Imperium National Bank, and the two have an immediate mutual attraction. Tom is a confirmed Yes man who just might hold the key to her biggest story, and to her heart.

programme.desc: When Rileys boyfriend, Mandla, invites her to South Africa to meet his family, she is shocked to discover that he is a prince. The news puts Rileys trust in Mandla in jeopardy, and he must do what he can to win her love back.

programme.title: Hunter and Twerp Scripture Seekers
programme.desc: Welcome to the wonderful world of Brightington, home of Hunter and Twerp, Scripture Seekers! Stacks of fun Bible lessons for children to enjoy. programme.desc: When interior decorator Zuri Maxwell meets a handsome benefactor and entrepreneur, she compromises the values and morals that should guide her, in an effort to be part of his world.

programme.title: Blonde and Blonder
programme.desc: When two dim-witted blonde bombshells are mistaken for the underworlds most cunning assassins, they are approached with a lucrative contract to take out the head of the Chinese mafia in a globetrotting, air-headed comedy. Two fair-haired beauties have just witnessed a high-profile mob hit, and now the Godfather is convinced that they have what it takes to rub out his most fearsome rival. After accepting a hearty payout and agreeing to carry out the dangerous assignment, the two brainless beauties hit the open road on the adventure of a lifetime.

programme.title: A Model Murder
programme.desc: Model Kara Woods begins to get disturbing messages from one of her fans, causing her to seek help from a security influencer. Things are fine until Karas stalker shows up in person.

programme.title: Betrayed By Love
programme.desc: Carrie becomes distraught when a car accident takes her sister Rileys life. As the investigation commences, she discovers that the accident might not be the true cause of Rileys death.

programme.title: Britney Ever After
programme.desc: This is the tumultuous true story of Britney Jean Spears, one of the bestselling teenage music artists of all-time, whose dating life and public emotional breakdowns were the subjects of a worldwide media frenzy. By the age of 21, Britney Spears already had a number one platinum, debut album, a cover on Rolling Stone, a record-breaking second album, and international superstardom. Success in her personal life, however, would be much harder to achieve. A well-publicized romance and break-up with Justin Timberlake, a three-day marriage to a childhood sweetheart, and an ill-fated marriage to back-up dancer Kevin Federline made for a chaotic contrast to her record-setting music career.

programme.title: Who Killed JonBenet?
programme.desc: This Lifetime Original Movie revisits the infamous murder of pint-sized beauty queen JonBenet Ramsey and the lurid details that captivated the nation. Starting with the 911 call and investigation lead by Detective Steve Thomas, the film provides a closer look into what exactly happened the day after Christmas 1996, when she was found beaten and strangled in the familys basement. With the addition of recently surfaced information, the film takes a fresh look at the events and the competing theories about the murder. Were Patsy and John Ramsey responsible or covering for someone else in the family? Was this a kidnapping gone wrong, or was this the work of a predator who had seen JonBen t in one of her pageants? Twenty years after the tragic events, the question remains: Who killed JonBenet?

programme.desc: Having been jilted at the altar, a literary aide to a controversial author thinks nothing of a fleeting liaison with a man she meets on a business flight.

programme.desc: Shane Settel starts to believe in fate after a chance tarot reading. He has the largest success in his professional career and falls in love, but then tragedies begin to follow him.

programme.desc: After the death of her husband, Ariels mother Dana finds a friend in the mysterious Adam. When Danas health starts to fail, Ariel suspects Adam might not have the best of intentions.

programme.desc: Expectant parents become prime suspects in the disappearance of a pregnant woman who was last seen at their garage sale.

programme.title: Expecting Amish
programme.desc: When an eventful Rumspringa leads to an unintended pregnancy, Amish teen Hannah must choose between returning to faith and family or beginning a new life elsewhere.

programme.title: Michael Jackson: Searching for Neverland
programme.desc: Based on Bill and Javons book Remember the Time: The Last Days of Michael Jackson, this movie will chronicle those intimate moments between Jackson and his children, document the professional turbulence that engulfed Jackson in financial trouble and forced him back to rehearsals for the ill-fated This Is It tour that led to his early death, and help answer the question that fans around the world want to know: What really happened to the King of Pop?

programme.desc: Joannas obsessive fantasy of a perfect life with Leo shatters, forcing her to confront harsh reality and the truth about their relationship, with dire consequences.

programme.desc: Alyssa has a relationship with abusive Steven as a teen, has his child but gives it up for adoption. Years later, their daughter seeks them out, and Steven manipulates her into an affair, neglecting his family.

programme.title: My Sisters Serial Killer Boyfriend
programme.desc: Maddie, a local reporter investigating a series of killings targeting similar looking women is caught off guard when her younger sister Olivia, is attacked in her own home. Urging on the side of caution, Maddie suggests they take a self defence course. When Olivia starts to fall for their instructor, Maddie becomes sceptical when he refuses to reveal anything about himself, and tries to intervene before the relationship turns into a deadly obsession.

programme.title: Single Black Female
programme.desc: Monica is a young host of one of LAs top morning shows. Reeling from the death of her beloved father and the breakup she just suffered, shes ready to focus on moving forward with her life, and channelling all of her energy into getting the new hosting gig on the afternoon talk show at her station. She gets a new assistant, Simone, a beautiful biracial woman who is new in town and so excited to be supporting Monica. They become close quickly, with Simone moving in next door, and engraining herself into Monicas life. But underneath Simones sweet exterior lies a woman who harbors a dark secret, and is determined to become closer than close to Monica, whether she likes it or not! As time goes on, and Simone becomes more and more enmeshed in Monicas life, Monica starts to pick up on the cracks in Simones shiny facade. As she tries to pull back from Simone, Monica and those around her begin to fear that it may be too late - and even worse, that Simone may have had something to do with the death of her father and collapse of her relationship! Monica decides to sever ties with Simone once and for all, however, Simone has other plans. Will Monica get her life back, or will Simone succeed in taking over Monicas life for good?

programme.title: See No Evil
programme.desc: Michelle Mockbee goes to work early to get a jumpstart on payroll. Less than an hour later, shes murdered outside her office. Surveillance footage leads detectives to a closet full of dirty secrets.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Just outside Memphis, an affluent Tennessee community is stunned when, in the early morning hours, a gentle, much-loved McDonalds manager is brutally attacked and left for dead on the floor of the restaurant. In critical condition, shes rushed to the hospital, where she dies soon after. In a town that prides itself on obeying the speed limit, the local police force goes into overdrive. The crime scene yields few clues, and with no signs of forced entry, investigators conclude the victim knew her killer. With a staggering list of possible suspects, including hundreds of former employees, the victims husband, and an eccentric cat-loving couple, investigators are baffled, and the case eventually goes cold. But nearly two years later, an anonymous tip finally brings them face to face with Delma Ramseys killers.

programme.title: Murder Detective
programme.desc: Former senior detective Graham Hill sheds new light on the inner workings, twists and turns of criminal investigations, showing how they were solved.

programme.title: New Scotland Yard Files
programme.desc: Its up to the detectives at New Scotland Yard to investigate the most mysterious and gripping murders in London. And now theyre opening their case files to tell the inside story of how they outsmarted the capitals most notorious killers.

programme.title: Australian Crime Stories
programme.desc: In 1969, Lucille Butterworth disappears from a bus stop in Tasmania. Seven years later, Geoffrey Charles Hunt confesses to the crime but despite damning evidence, police did not lay charges.

programme.title: The First 48
programme.desc: In Memphis, Sergeants Mundy Quinn and Kevin Lundy set up a sting to catch the victims killer. In Miami, Detective Manny Castillo and Sgt Juan Herrera are called to a brazen execution in the middle of a bustling neighbourhood in Coconut Grove.

programme.title: See No Evil
programme.desc: A young couple on their way home from a night of birthday celebrations is gunned down while getting gas. With the killers long since vanished, detectives must rely on the grainy gas station video.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Its July 30, 1995, a scorching San Diego summer day. An unidentified young woman is discovered by the side of the road, naked, raped, strangled to death, and thrown out like a piece of trash. Police have few clues but waste little time investigating this haunting crime. DNA matches the victim to 18-year-old Shannon Conway, a troubled teenage runaway who was living out of a sleeping bag among the hippies and transients on San Diegos Ocean Beach. An initial sweep zeroes in on several suspects. Tim Arman, Shannons ex-boyfriend, is still bitter that she dumped him a year ago. Keith Martin, a hobo living out of his van, is known as an angry Vietnam vet with a grudge against women. Martins van, eerily splattered with blood, was spotted in the area on the night of the murder. Police become convinced Martin is the killer but they cant forensically link him to the crime. Then a third suspect enters the frame. The day before Shannon was killed, she jumped into a pickup truck with a man she had met minutes before. Despite three strong leads, the San Diego Homicide struggle to put all the pieces together. Until over a decade later, new advances in DNA testing help cold case investigators finally find Shannons killer and give closure to her heart-broken mother.

programme.title: Cops Reloaded
programme.desc: Cops Reloaded revisits some of the most memorable suspects, car chases and action-packed moments from televisions popular reality program.

programme.title: Cops
programme.desc: Television cameras follow real-life law enforcement officers and capture the action as they perform their daily duty to serve and protect the public.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Australia
programme.desc: On the 14 July 2001, British couple Peter Falconio and Joanne Lees stopped on the Stuart Highway in the Northern Territory after a man flagged down their car. This man, later identified as Bradley Murdoch, supposedly shot Falconio before tying Lees up and covering her head. She managed to escape while Murdoch was distracted, hiding in nearby bushes for five hours until she was able to run out into the road and flag down a truck driver who took her to safety. Falconios body has never been found. The subsequent trial and media furore would stun the nation as well as raising questions about the strength of the allegations against Murdoch.

programme.title: Crime Investigation Australia
programme.sub-title: Date With A Serial Killer - Rodney Cameron
programme.desc: Rodney Francis Cameron was dubbed The Lonely Hearts Killer after he used a radio matchmaking program in 1990 to lure an unsuspecting woman to her death. Incredibly, he had only just been released from prison for two other killings in 1974. Camerons psychopathic tendencies appeared early in his life. At the age of 10 he tried to strangle a young girl. He then attempted to strangle two other women and moved into a life of alcohol and drug abuse, including experimenting with hallucinogenic chemicals. He also dabbled in Satanism.

programme.title: #textmewhenyougethome
programme.desc: #TextMeWhenYouGetHome became a viral, worldwide movement following the 2021 death of Sarah Everard. The slogan sparked awareness around the vulnerability women feel while out in public alone.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: On August 15, 1998, in the small village of Omagh in County Tyrone, Northern Ireland, a car bomb was detonated in the main shopping area. Twenty-nine people, including a pregnant woman and her two unborn babies, died as a result. Victims included children, Catholics and Protestants, and visitors from the Republic of Ireland and Spain. Three days after the attack, the Real IRA (RIRA) claimed responsibility. Although one man was charged and later convicted with the crime, he was released in 2005 due to evidence that the Gardai had tampered with his interview. To this day, nobody has been convicted for the crime. There have been allegations of a cover-up by the police force on both sides of the border, and of a lacklustre performance in the investigation by the then Royal Ulster Constabulary (now the Police Service of Northern Ireland). A civil case brought by members of the victims families claimed that Michael McKevitt, Liam Campbell, Colm Murphy and Seamus Daly were guilty of the bombings, and they were held liable for 1.6 million pounds of damages.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Australia
programme.desc: On the 14 July 2001, British couple Peter Falconio and Joanne Lees stopped on the Stuart Highway in the Northern Territory after a man flagged down their car. She managed to escape while Murdoch was distracted, hiding in nearby bushes for five hours until she was able to run out into the road and flag down a truck driver who took her to safety. Falconios body has never been found. The subsequent trial and media furore would stun the nation as well as raising questions about the strength of the allegations against Murdoch.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Lower Puna, Big Island, Hawaii, is a sun-kissed tropical playground drawing thousands of tourists. But in the shadows lurks another story of drugs, crime, and brutal violence. The two worlds collide on Christmas Eve, 1991, when 23-year-old tourist Dana Ireland takes a bike ride through paradise that ends in tragedy. Hit by a car, raped, and left for dead on a remote trail, Danas murder devastates her family and sends ripples of fear throughout the state. Police investigate a murky world few tourists ever see but come up empty. From the get-go, the police investigation is fraught. The crime scene evidence is messy, forensic technology cant connect the dots, and most suspects or witnesses are either tight-lipped or flat-out lying. When Danas father, furious with the polices lack of results, posts a $28,000 reward for any leads, lowlife tipsters come crawling out of the woodwork and overwhelm police with false information. Lead Detective, Steve Guillermo, is certain of only one fact - a small car struck Danas bike. The search for this vehicle takes over six years but upon finding it, Guillermo starts to untangle the web of lies. Three weeks before a statute of limitations ends on the prime suspects, Guillermo gets a break that closes the case for good.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: In February 2000, eight-year-old Victoria Climbie died at St Marys Hospital, Middlesex. She had suffered the worst case of child abuse ever seen in the UK, at the hands of her aunt, Marie Therese Kouao, and an acquaintance, Carl Manning. Victoria had 128 separate injuries, which social services had failed to notice and act upon. As a result of her murder, the government conducted the biggest overhaul of the child protection service the UK had ever seen. The inquiry that followed took the unusual step of calling both Manning and Kouao to give evidence to try to understand how the authorities had failed Victoria so badly.

She managed to escape while Murdoch was distracted, hiding in nearby bushes for five hours until she was able to run out into the road and flag down a truck driver who took her to safety. Falconios body has never been found. The subsequent trial and media furore would stun the nation as well as raising questions about the strength of the allegations against Murdoch.

programme.title: Crime Investigation Australia
programme.sub-title: Date With A Serial Killer - Rodney Cameron
programme.desc: Rodney Francis Cameron was dubbed The Lonely Hearts Killer after he used a radio matchmaking program in 1990 to lure an unsuspecting woman to her death. Incredibly, he had only just been released from prison for two other killings in 1974. Camerons psychopathic tendencies appeared early in his life. At the age of 10 he tried to strangle a young girl. He then attempted to strangle two other women and moved into a life of alcohol and drug abuse, including experimenting with hallucinogenic chemicals. He also dabbled in Satanism.

programme.title: #textmewhenyougethome
programme.desc: #TextMeWhenYouGetHome became a viral, worldwide movement following the 2021 death of Sarah Everard. The slogan sparked awareness around the vulnerability women feel while out in public alone.

programme.title: See No Evil
programme.desc: A young couple on their way home from a night of birthday celebrations is gunned down while getting gas. With the killers long since vanished, detectives must rely on the grainy gas station video.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Its July 30, 1995, a scorching San Diego summer day. An unidentified young woman is discovered by the side of the road, naked, raped, strangled to death, and thrown out like a piece of trash. Police have few clues but waste little time investigating this haunting crime. DNA matches the victim to 18-year-old Shannon Conway, a troubled teenage runaway who was living out of a sleeping bag among the hippies and transients on San Diegos Ocean Beach. An initial sweep zeroes in on several suspects. Tim Arman, Shannons ex-boyfriend, is still bitter that she dumped him a year ago. Keith Martin, a hobo living out of his van, is known as an angry Vietnam vet with a grudge against women. Martins van, eerily splattered with blood, was spotted in the area on the night of the murder. Police become convinced Martin is the killer but they cant forensically link him to the crime. Then a third suspect enters the frame. The day before Shannon was killed, she jumped into a pickup truck with a man she had met minutes before. Despite three strong leads, the San Diego Homicide struggle to put all the pieces together. Until over a decade later, new advances in DNA testing help cold case investigators finally find Shannons killer and give closure to her heart-broken mother.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Lower Puna, Big Island, Hawaii, is a sun-kissed tropical playground drawing thousands of tourists. But in the shadows lurks another story of drugs, crime, and brutal violence. The two worlds collide on Christmas Eve, 1991, when 23-year-old tourist Dana Ireland takes a bike ride through paradise that ends in tragedy. Hit by a car, raped, and left for dead on a remote trail, Danas murder devastates her family and sends ripples of fear throughout the state. Police investigate a murky world few tourists ever see but come up empty. From the get-go, the police investigation is fraught. The crime scene evidence is messy, forensic technology cant connect the dots, and most suspects or witnesses are either tight-lipped or flat-out lying. When Danas father, furious with the polices lack of results, posts a $28,000 reward for any leads, lowlife tipsters come crawling out of the woodwork and overwhelm police with false information. Lead Detective, Steve Guillermo, is certain of only one fact - a small car struck Danas bike. The search for this vehicle takes over six years but upon finding it, Guillermo starts to untangle the web of lies. Three weeks before a statute of limitations ends on the prime suspects, Guillermo gets a break that closes the case for good.

programme.title: Booked: First Day In
programme.desc: Follows arrested individuals through Americas booking process, offering an extraordinary look at the most unusual, bizarre and often tense bookings. Every day in America around 25,000 people are arrested and booked into jail, each one-hour episode will follow the story of an arrestee, with their permission, as they move through the system and recount what ultimately led them to their time in jail. From petty offences to serious crimes, viewers will be taken on a harrowing adventure while they watch the arrestees throughout the booking process.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: In February 2000, eight-year-old Victoria Climbie died at St Marys Hospital, Middlesex. She had suffered the worst case of child abuse ever seen in the UK, at the hands of her aunt, Marie Therese Kouao, and an acquaintance, Carl Manning. Victoria had 128 separate injuries, which social services had failed to notice and act upon. As a result of her murder, the government conducted the biggest overhaul of the child protection service the UK had ever seen. The inquiry that followed took the unusual step of calling both Manning and Kouao to give evidence to try to understand how the authorities had failed Victoria so badly.

The death of Reeves second wife, Sharon, had been ruled a suicide, but blood spatter evidence in a photo indicated she might have been murdered. An autopsy, performed on Sharons body 14 years after her death, revealed even more.

programme.title: Forensic Files
programme.desc: A lifelong resident of the tiny town of Lefroy, Tasmania, was murdered outside his own home. Robbery appeared to be the motive, but with no suspects, the investigation came to a halt. programme.title: Forensic Files

programme.title: Churchill
programme.desc: This definitive six-part series will explore every facet of Britains most legendary prime minster. Well reveal the secrets of his aristocratic upbringing, his formative years in the military, his rise to political power, his wartime leadership and his legacy. Well look at his biggest triumphs, most disastrous defeats and reflect on his lasting legacy.

programme.title: Hitler: Countdown to War
programme.desc: This episode reveals how Hitler manipulated and played games with the Czechs and with the western powers of Britain and France to achieve his ends.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: During WWII, one and two-man crews aboard dangerous and stealthy mini-weapons could threaten the largest battleships at anchor. We examine Italian human torpedoes - torpedoes outfitted with controls and a seat for their drivers - that crippled the British fleet at Alexandria and Gibraltar; to Japanese mini-subs that unsuccessfully struck at Pearl Harbor; and British mini-subs that attacked the German battleship Tirpitz.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: At the end of the Vietnam War, the USS Midways pilots and airmen engaged in some of the most thrilling and intense air combat. Six F4 Phantoms launched from the deck of the USS Midway engage with North Vietnamese MiGs. The Phantoms destroy two MiGs. Watch as American pilots Bartholomay and Arwood down enemy MiG-19s over their home base at Kep. Then flight lead Vic Kovaleski brings down a MiG-17, scoring the last MiG kill of the war. Midway served honourably throughout Vietnam and even in Desert Storm, but time finally caught up with her, and the USS Midway was converted to a museum and now resides in San Diego, California.

programme.title: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: By July 1943, the full extent of Hitlers failed gamble in the East had become clear. After failing to deliver knockout blows at Stalingrad and Moscow, his army was now at the mercy of the vast Soviet war machine. With its huge resources and seemingly limitless numbers of men, the Red Army slowly pushed the Germans back out of Russia through Ukraine, Poland, the Balkans and Hungary. This was war on a monster scale, pitching armies of millions against each other. But it was also a war fought by small bands of partisans, men like Tito in Yugoslavia, leading guerrilla bands against Nazi forces. Conventional wisdom has recently changed as more and more secrets have been revealed particularly in the last five to 10 years as documents, files and photographs have been released. Code-breaking revelations and newly released government papers on both sides of the Atlantic have added a very insightful new dimension to the understanding of this, the worlds greatest ever conflict. With the very latest satellite-delivered terrain mapping and state-of-the-art graphics, this story can now be told with the very latest access to information which was not previously available.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters
programme.desc: The hunt for, Franz Stangl, the Nazi commandant of the Treblinka and Sobibor death camps in Poland. He was responsible for the extermination of around 900,000 men, women and children. At the end of the war, he escaped to Italy where he joined a rat-line organised by Vatican officials. From there, he disappeared.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.sub-title: Every Castle Needs A Lord, Henley In Arden
programme.desc: A castle reputedly as grand and important as Warwick once dominated the Midlands village of Henley-in-Arden. Now there is just a hill. An eccentric American millionaire has bought himself the title of Lord of the Manor, and hes desperate to know what his castle might have looked like in its Norman and medieval heydays. After three days, 10 trenches and one archery contest, Tony Robinson and the team believe they have the answer.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: Among the first US Navy vessels to see action in the Pacific in WWII were the motor torpedo boats of PT Boat Squadron 3 in the Philippines during the Japanese invasion. And for the next three years, from Guadalcanal to the coasts of Japan, they ran reconnaissance and screening missions, landed raiding parties, and attacked enemy shore installations and supply barges. See how they lived up to the motto of John Paul Jones: "Give me a fast ship, for I intend to go in harms way."

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: In the aerial battleground of World War II, the P-51 Mustang proved itself to be the most famous war bird in history. Take a look at three of its most memorable battles. On November 2, 1944, Capt Donald Bryan leads a group of P-51s escorting B-24 bombers to their target deep inside of Germany when he runs into a huge gaggle of Me109s on the attack. On June 23, 1945, 2d Lt Bob Scamara takes off with a flight of Mustangs from Iwo Jima. His group is jumped by 17 Zeroes. On April 7, 1945, pilot Richard Candelaria becomes one of the first Americans to face the jet menace.

programme.title: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Today it is easy to see D-Day as an inevitable - a straightforward victory against a German army that was already all but defeated. This film explodes that myth. It charts the careful planning of the campaign, the development of specialised equipment needed for the amphibious landing. It reveals the deception plan that wrong-footed Hitler. It shows how the Americans were very nearly driven off Omaha beach. If that had happened, the whole operation might have failed. The film ends with the liberation of Paris, as the Free French forces led by Charles de Gaulle marched down the streets of the capital. programme.title: The Crusaders: Fortresses of Faith

programme.title: Digging For Britain
programme.desc: In the West, one of the largest Roman buildings ever discovered in Britain, an Iron Age chariot is saved, and evidence is found of the transatlantic slave trade in Devon.

programme.title: Churchill
programme.desc: This definitive six-part series will explore every facet of Britains most legendary prime minster. Well reveal the secrets of his aristocratic upbringing, his formative years in the military, his rise to political power, his wartime leadership and his legacy. Well look at his biggest triumphs, most disastrous defeats and reflect on his lasting legacy.

programme.title: Hitler: Countdown to War
programme.desc: This episode reveals how Hitler manipulated and played games with the Czechs and with the western powers of Britain and France to achieve his ends.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: During WWII, one and two-man crews aboard dangerous and stealthy mini-weapons could threaten the largest battleships at anchor. We examine Italian human torpedoes - torpedoes outfitted with controls and a seat for their drivers - that crippled the British fleet at Alexandria and Gibraltar; to Japanese mini-subs that unsuccessfully struck at Pearl Harbor; and British mini-subs that attacked the German battleship Tirpitz.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: At the end of the Vietnam War, the USS Midways pilots and airmen engaged in some of the most thrilling and intense air combat. Six F4 Phantoms launched from the deck of the USS Midway engage with North Vietnamese MiGs. The Phantoms destroy two MiGs. Watch as American pilots Bartholomay and Arwood down enemy MiG-19s over their home base at Kep. Then flight lead Vic Kovaleski brings down a MiG-17, scoring the last MiG kill of the war. Midway served honourably throughout Vietnam and even in Desert Storm, but time finally caught up with her, and the USS Midway was converted to a museum and now resides in San Diego, California.

programme.title: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: By July 1943, the full extent of Hitlers failed gamble in the East had become clear. After failing to deliver knockout blows at Stalingrad and Moscow, his army was now at the mercy of the vast Soviet war machine. With its huge resources and seemingly limitless numbers of men, the Red Army slowly pushed the Germans back out of Russia through Ukraine, Poland, the Balkans and Hungary. This was war on a monster scale, pitching armies of millions against each other. But it was also a war fought by small bands of partisans, men like Tito in Yugoslavia, leading guerrilla bands against Nazi forces. Conventional wisdom has recently changed as more and more secrets have been revealed particularly in the last five to 10 years as documents, files and photographs have been released. Code-breaking revelations and newly released government papers on both sides of the Atlantic have added a very insightful new dimension to the understanding of this, the worlds greatest ever conflict. With the very latest satellite-delivered terrain mapping and state-of-the-art graphics, this story can now be told with the very latest access to information which was not previously available.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters
programme.desc: The hunt for, Franz Stangl, the Nazi commandant of the Treblinka and Sobibor death camps in Poland. He was responsible for the extermination of around 900,000 men, women and children. At the end of the war, he escaped to Italy where he joined a rat-line organised by Vatican officials. From there, he disappeared.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.sub-title: Every Castle Needs A Lord, Henley In Arden
programme.desc: A castle reputedly as grand and important as Warwick once dominated the Midlands village of Henley-in-Arden. Now there is just a hill. An eccentric American millionaire has bought himself the title of Lord of the Manor, and hes desperate to know what his castle might have looked like in its Norman and medieval heydays. After three days, 10 trenches and one archery contest, Tony Robinson and the team believe they have the answer.

But when Allie reconciles with her boyfriend, their unspoken bargain goes terrifyingly awry. Instincts dont come baser than this.

programme.title: Mr Inbetween

For Ray, its all about respect. Ray brings Ally home to meet Brittany. Ray cant sleep and gets up to notice a van parked outside surveilling his house. He goes for a drive and leads the van out to a safe place to do some permanent damage to its occupants - Davros guys - using the surprise Gary gave him.

programme.desc: Gary wakes from his coma, and thanks Ray for doing "a bit of this and a bit of that" to Vassili and the guys who bashed him. Ray and Nick are becoming friends and he asks Nick for a favour. Jacinta berates Ray for telling Brittany that Jesus isnt real. The court has ordered Ray to attend anger management. His first meeting doesnt go very well. Freddy informs Ray that the guys he bashed for putting Gary in a coma belong to a crew run by his son-in-laws brother, Davros. Freddy insists Ray sits down with Davros to smooth the waters. Nick makes good on the favour. While on drugs, Vasilli breaks into Garys house to rob the contents of his safe. Gary, who has just returned home from hospital, manages to send an SOS text to Ray who is out shopping with Ally. Ray comes to Garys rescue and promptly deals with Vasilli - but theyll have to work out what to do with the body as Tatiana has arrived home unexpectedly.

programme.title: Mr Inbetween
programme.desc: Gary takes Ray for a drive to give him a surprise as a thank you for saving him. Ray and Allys relationship has developed. Freddy takes Ray to meet Davros. Ray doesnt like Davros and although Davros seems placated by the end of the conference, Freddy knows better. A road-rage incident forces Ally to confront Ray about his quick access to violence, rather than attempting to diffuse a situation. When court-ordered anger management therapist Peter confronts Ray about the same impulse, Ray explains that its justifiable to let people clearly know that there are ramifications for being an a******. For Ray, its all about respect. Ray brings Ally home to meet Brittany. Ray cant sleep and gets up to notice a van parked outside surveilling his house. He goes for a drive and leads the van out to a safe place to do some permanent damage to its occupants - Davros guys - using the surprise Gary gave him.
